Here's the pattern using MAUI's lifecycle events and `Preferences` for lightweight persistence:

**In your `App.xaml.cs`** — hook the lifecycle events:

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public App()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        MainPage = new NavigationPage(new NotePage());
    }

    protected override void OnSleep()
    {
        // App going to background — notify the page to save
        MessagingCenter.Send(this, "SaveDraft");
    }

    protected override void OnResume()
    {
        // App returning — notify the page to restore
        MessagingCenter.Send(this, "RestoreDraft");
    }
}
```

**In your `NotePage.xaml.cs`** — save and restore the draft:

```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "NoteDraft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "SaveDraft", _ => SaveDraft());
        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "RestoreDraft", _ => RestoreDraft());

        // Restore any existing draft on first load
        RestoreDraft();
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    public void ClearDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "SaveDraft");
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "RestoreDraft");
    }
}
```

**In your `NotePage.xaml`:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             x:Class="YourApp.NotePage">
    <Editor x:Name="NoteEditor"
            Placeholder="Start typing your note..." />
</ContentPage>
```

### Key points

| Concept | Detail |
|---|---|
| **`OnSleep`** | Fires when app backgrounds — save here |
| **`OnResume`** | Fires when app returns — restore here |
| **`Preferences`** | Key-value store, perfect for small text drafts |
| **Cleanup** | Unsubscribe in `OnDisappearing` to avoid leaks |
| **Clear draft** | Call `ClearDraft()` after the user explicitly saves the note |

> **Note:** `MessagingCenter` is deprecated in .NET 8+. For newer projects, use the `WeakReferenceMessenger` from the [CommunityToolkit.Mvvm](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/communitytoolkit/mvvm/messenger) package — same pattern, just swap `MessagingCenter` for `WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Register/Send`.
